This is free and open source software, released under the
General Public License 3. Please see the file COPYING for details.

The license sets the requirements for using this software.
The requirements in this section are not legally binding; 
however, they represent things that the author would appreciate: 
If you write a paper based on work that uses this software, 
please include a citation to one of our papers, and send a copy 
of your paper. If you create a derivative work based on a this 
software, tell me about it and let me know how I can get a 
copy, and include this request if itâ€™s appropriate.

The algorithms in this software are described in the papers below. 
Feel free to cite the paper that seems more appropriate:

  Timo Baumann (2008).
  "Simulating Spoken Dialogue With a Focus on Realistic Turn-Taking".
  in Proceedings of the 13th ESSLLI Student Session, Hamburg, Germany.
  http://www.ling.uni-potsdam.de/~timo/pub/bababa.pdf
  
  Gabriel Skantze and David Schlangen (2009).
  "Incremental Dialogue Processing in a Micro-Domain".
  in Proceedings of EACL, Athens, Greece.
  http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/E/E09/E09-1085.pdf

